Rearranging: $t^2 - 2t - 1 \leq 0$, which is true for $t \in [1 - \sqrt{2}, 1 + \sqrt{2}]$. Since $t \geq 1$, this holds for $t \in [1, 1 + \sqrt{2}]$.

